Introduction

IWR1642BOOST EVM antenna is designed to be operated in 77GHz to 81GHz frequency range. The use cases which can be addressed with this antenna are traffic monitoring, outdoor people counting, motion detection, perimeter security, surveillance etc.

Design Azimuth FOV (deg)* Elevation FOV (deg)* Azimuth Angular Resolution(deg) Elevation Angular Resolution (deg) Max Distance for Person (m) **
IWR1642BOOST (77GHz) +/-60 +/-15 15 N/A 90

A comparison table of all antenna configurations can be on the Antennas overview page.

IWR1642BOOST EVM Antenna Picture & Dimensions

The antenna peak gain of IWR1642BOOST EVM Antenna is about 10.5 dBi across the operating frequency band of 76 to 81 GHz.

For more details about this EVM, please refer to the following link:
http://www.ti.com/tool/iwr1642boost

IWR1642BOOST EVM Stackup

Please refer to below PCB stackup details for IWR1642BOOST Antenna.

The mmWave layer is Rogers RO4835 with LoPro copper. ED (electro-deposited) copper is not a suitable material for mmWave frequencies.

Detailed layout of this antenna with stackup are available for you to download and reuse at the following link: http://www.ti.com/lit/zip/sprr255
